Four people were left injured following a collision between a truck and a bakkie on the N3 before the Mariannhill toll plaza on Wednesday .On arrival ER24 paramedics found the bakkie in the emergency lane and the truck still on the road.ER24 Spokesperson Robert Mckenzie said the driver of the bakkie and three other occupants were assessed and found to have sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate.All patients were treated and transported to hospital for further medical care.The cause of the incident is unknown.&nbsp;&nbsp;-TNA Reporter